        "content": "We need to implement the next module: Calibration. This module stores dry/wet thresholds in NVS (Non-Volatile Storage) so they persist across reboots. It should provide functions to read thresholds, set thresholds, and a calibration routine.\n\nLet's implement Calibration.h and Calibration.cpp. We'll use Preferences library (Arduino wrapper over NVS) to store dry and wet values. The class should have:\n- begin() - initialize NVS namespace\n- getDryValue() / getWetValue() - retrieve from NVS\n- setDryValue(uint16_t) / setWetValue(uint16_t) - save to NVS\n- calibrateDry() - set current sensor reading as dry threshold\n- calibrateWet() - set current sensor reading as wet threshold\n- resetToDefaults() - set default values\n\nWe also need to make the Sensor class use the Calibration class? Or keep them separate and have main pass thresholds. Better to keep them decoupled: Sensor takes dry/wet as parameters, Calibration stores and retrieves them. Main reads thresholds from Calibration and passes to Sensor.\n\nLet's implement.",
