        "command": "Implement the WebServer module for WiFi connection and REST API.\n\nFile: lib/WebServer/WebServer.h\n- Class WebServer\n- Constructor takes Sensor*, Calibration*, Display* references for callbacks\n- begin() - start WiFi AP mode (or connect to saved WiFi), start web server on port 80\n- handleClient() - call in loop\n- stop() - stop server\n- Private:\n  - AsyncWebServer server;\n  - AsyncEventSource events; // for SSE updates\n  - Sensor* m_sensor;\n  - Calibration* m_calibration;\n  - Display* m_display;\n  - WiFi credentials storage using Preferences\n  - method setupAP() - start access point with captive portal\n  - method connectToSavedWiFi() - try saved credentials\n  - method setupRoutes() - define all API endpoints\n\nAPI Endpoints:\n- GET /api/status -> JSON: {moisture: %, raw: int, voltage: float, dry: int, wet: int, wifi: \"connected\"}\n- POST /api/calibrate/dry -> set current reading as dry threshold\n- POST /api/calibrate/wet -> set current reading as wet threshold\n- POST /api/calibrate/reset -> reset to defaults\n- GET /api/calibration -> get current dry/wet values\n- GET /wifi -> HTML page for WiFi configuration (captive portal)\n- POST /wifi/connect -> save WiFi credentials and restart\n- Root / -> redirect to /wifi or show simple status page\n\nFile: lib/WebServer/WebServer.cpp\n- Include <ESPAsyncWebServer.h>, <AsyncTCP.h>, <WiFi.h>, <Preferences.h>, <ArduinoJson.h>, <DNSServer.h> for captive portal\n- In begin(): \n  1. Read saved WiFi credentials from Preferences (namespace \"wifi\").\n  2. If saved ssid exists, try to connect (WiFi.begin(ssid, pass)) with timeout 10s.\n  3. If no saved credentials or connection fails, start AP mode with SSID \"Polivator-Config\" and captive portal.\n  4. Setup all routes.\n  5. Start server.\n- setupRoutes(): define handlers for each API endpoint\n- In handleClient(): nothing needed for AsyncWebServer (it's async), but can call dnsServer.processNextRequest() if using captive portal\n- For captive portal: use DNSServer to redirect all requests to the AP IP (192.168.4.1).\n- For JSON responses: use AsyncResponseStream or ArduinoJson to serialize.\n\nEnsure to add ESPAsyncWebServer and AsyncTCP to lib_deps in platformio.ini (already done). Also add DNSServer for captive portal (built-in).",
